SIMPLE: define
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Define
<hw>De*fine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Defined</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Defining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>definer</ets>,
usually, to end, to finish, F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧finir</ets> to define, L.
<ets>definire</ets> to limit, define; <ets>de-</ets> + <ets>finire</ets>
to limit, end, <ets>finis</ets> boundary, limit, end. See
<er>Final</er>, <er>Finish</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To fix the
bounds of; to bring to a termination; to end.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To
<xex>define</xex> controversies.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To determine or clearly exhibit the boundaries of;
to mark the limits of; <as>as, to <ex>define</ex> the extent of a
kingdom or country</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To determine with precision; to mark out with
distinctness; to ascertain or exhibit clearly; <as>as, the
<ex>defining</ex> power of an optical instrument</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rings . . . very distinct and well <qex>defined</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir I. Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To determine the precise signification of; to fix
the meaning of; to describe accurately; to explain; to expound or
interpret; <as>as, to <ex>define</ex> a word, a phrase, or a scientific
term</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They <qex>define</qex> virtue to be life ordered according to
nature.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson (More's Utopia).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Define</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Define
<hw>De*fine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To determine; to
decide.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Definement</ent>⟦br⟧
